cies added will be included correctly during runtime.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Inspecting native image capabilities**\\n\\nI'm thinking about whether the native image supports URLClassLoader. It seems like it does, but only if the classes are in jar files on disk. In native test execution, I wonder if the original classpath jars are actually on the classpath since the executable is standalone. I'm not exactly sure about this. I should check the reachability metadata to see if it includes all necessary elements for the current classpath.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_CEMpq9QLh1aXZWdhMul4N5Sm|fc_08701a54876117250169f39d5c5c6c81a1ac2589382ebf7185", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "metadata/com.diffplug.spotless/spotless-lib/2.45.0/reachability-metadata.json"}, "partialJson": "{\"path\":\"metadata/com.diffplug.spotless/spotless-lib/2.45.0/reachability-metadata.json\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 4991, "output": 1031, "cacheRead": 31744, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 37766, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777573193094, "responseId": "resp_08701a54876117250169f39d4a388881a1b629fdcf2644746d"}}
