[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Exploring native image challenges**\n\nI'm considering adding a build argument, IncludeResources=ktfmt/.*. If the resource jars are massive, that could be an issue. I wonder if I need native reflection metadata for the URLClassLoader to load the ktfmt internals. The dynamic access report focuses on KtfmtStep, but the actual ktfmt code might require reflection as well. Executing ktfmt in native may present problems since native images can't load new bytecode at runtime. Dynamic class loading from external jars isn't supported either. It looks like this library's dynamic loading is what's under scrutiny.\n\n**Analyzing GraalVM native image limitations**\n\nI'm realizing that with GraalVM native image, all classes must be known at build time, so defining new classes at runtime might not be possible. But I'm uncertain if the `nativeTestCompile` runs tests properly. The user mentioned that tests execute under a native image, possibly including KtfmtStep. There’s reachability metadata without any configuration. The dynamic access coverage generated by `nativeTestCompile` likely comes from the agent during JVM tests. I need to ensure our tests work with the native executable and dynamically loaded external classes; otherwise, they might fail.\n\n**Considering native image dynamics**\n\nI'm pondering if native images can define glue classes. It seems that if the metadata configuration includes certain classes, the classloader might resolve them properly. Still, since the native image doesn't support `defineClass`, this could lead to failure. The existing source uses a feature classloader from Spotless, possibly making it workable via reachability metadata. Given the user’s request to improve dynamic access, I think the tests should focus on creating formatter functions without applying them. However, FormatterStep.format both creates and applies, so maybe I should just call `step.getName()` instead to avoid creating state.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_08701a54876117250169f39d871b1881a1892bb0415fedc82a\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp852VEvIRq0NNOWVax_FGqIRiCQ3TLmpgudMQhdWPy2jrLf1gyIZ3UB65I75LKh4bbF-mRU9t1CemB6jTxZygvg5AjqJi5_ma3M-pLsdbQCH_1_lhz5B9RxS8W0_KfUOw0YE2bok6BfSeeqjVw-W8noxo3l2ErOTTCxADhgvNkoFuMOwuMsB_Xg6aO4C84OT8qGmVPhQlEFROSbslJEuUXItNpkJwTDbPsWZkH8ZZ0KpAqYBzcY6y2nf1RDRW8S3QPJvIVqJa6df5UpI3FTLFu_bPS4oGK9gs3VJpzQYMl22jaBhuLKpuj_9q1pmS7uH-25DRb5hUyQePdfLQzsgp0S1NUMCnJd_WIckzJkoBk0rVlQHa-Mw3jNLxkuFPlG-sxn7WNkpWAlwF_jMNaGv2oqMjNn84zqZzbZThvXaeurIp7gSqHfNSggZ5Cr9wsdnl5UqmSEWgpwjmFmILcNGsmQeFokwGfztcSf10XiU_3v_DbAdlgSN30xjl-m32NJOfa-SjUK0l6TYn9T1kSkoC2q_aCY4keis9YOPqg5e0-au1hdNbREzKQv8etcVoLcSwNzbRlajOxMWSOblqUDTgfu3WFNfuLQgYc5v6P-CBAIhQkQjey5VvUDoGNbWCSGZTVem5cKgbnnangRTWAWDFnIXsN81RZJT1tf0pnLfUv3P5WlP1pVOhqNzhlB2RDJIkdYmqWd5mOPq6fLs2WeAPQ0VUUKDxYsWc8gaQd3GuNl9l8fQnt3T3_cLMqaosuX3-DMhxKiaErC5Jj0tsxGDtmO2U0sOtJlIGpubhFPVcDN8JWjlzRVm2ep1tgtEzBjbECzJdLxPsCv1p6dW5_7kCnVxLX4MU34aAL9XYeK8EmK3zcGg-mz3MDARQG4WqaFQVnXVkGK16YFKGyCczAeSbpbXnV6Tr9_W38-jVh4KLUz18j4mC2tF7i_kB9HT-jrdowSOKNubhUnf2dzf04Vlt2gc1eysQNlhYH8X1O-PxSsJXKdqG55iGCnXWMbq_kTAWqnI_hRqPflQSIF8ZuOF6zJ9jNVr5mzpUCdcMPfL9rtSob9xq1x_R8s79GZwB5e3SDrVCoRvQAjNbPUQz1JvVuwfI6u60dkHP1waok-4p0bhVwBGuAxTT1GgbFM_DS7rPFAQ1cLzeCp3dzkOVNl8Pkuf3dK64skCBeLOow5jnZJkMqplNNHXQPyBMGojDxixcRFesgFd7pTuYRVOs9N_PE_xZBgmm98Vo-NFzcA761X64_updyIzSeFJhRKgNXM2F232u97ZLStGzGffXpISTaqDlv8r2_9hqbtkyzP4iD5MNW_UfZd0-pxe_y6c0qvt9zwkOk7sVDyXVND4XeZK_5NnlzZ0aBba1SBbAlO2qfEXK51Wdgt28lYrl3j8aYJtXQImknaXGhfsyshk_fYkzRQEFy2Z-5cfs3_KHvxVKS1YwdMdRGE_QGMa7ZqtPvnW0pvO1NdHM4JQT2zGsNdZSw1vGpxb59J5nJV1H75fZbCxpjuTV0FyVFEeJTOduPIv0DhKOoEyz-lUDc_o8gLm0gpCfuqqhfgRug5DTQrJqWMJzOxQbSPN2fkE4RPYJfyRcIoGrDTl6F6oRIcQp6eNuQytJoD_pN-amj4e6ZES2MeanTLO1npSOpoZenf8fxBUNDCr5pRSpfjkOB9jeus-KFvFvheaefE3YHLs-0iMQ4en2CEBb4VMnJg4aGRPf010sx9ydJnC028Eco1wc7m8dxygMkO92cn0z5ehCLrxPFE88T_xiiWcDV9_TzuucsHcUyTgR5